 1.Write MATLAB code to perform the following:
 Addition of two numbers: x = 15, y = 5
 Multiplication of two numbers: a = 7, b = 3
 Subtraction of two numbers: m = 20, n = 8

 MATLABCode:
 x =15;
 y =5;
 sum_result = x + y; % Addition
 a = 7;
 b =3;
 mul_result = a * b; % Multiplication
 m=20;
 n =8;
 sub_result = m- n; % Subtraction
 %Display results
 disp(['Sum: ', num2str(sum_result)]);
 disp(['Multiplication: ', num2str(mul_result)]);
 disp(['Subtraction: ', num2str(sub_result)]);

 1.Write MATLAB codeto perform element-wise multiplication and division on two arrays
 A=[10, 20, 30] and B = [2, 4, 5].
 MATLABCode:
 A=[10, 20, 30];
 B=[2, 4, 5];
 %Element-wise multiplication and division
 mul_result = A .* B; % Element-wise multiplication
 div_result = A ./ B; % Element-wise division
 %Display results
 disp('Element-wise multiplication:');
 disp(mul_result);
 disp('Element-wise division:');
 disp(div_result);
